 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Hamiltonian</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Several 2c relativistic Hamiltonians are available in RAQET, which are summarized in Table 
  <a rid="jcc25364-tbl-0001" ref-type="table" href="#jcc25364-tbl-0001">1</a>. For the one‐electron parts, 
  <div id="nlm-math-15" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <div class="msubsup">
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">h</span>
     <span class="mn">2</span>
     <span class="mo">+</span>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> of the 2c relativistic Hamiltonian in eq. (
  <a rid="jcc25364-disp-0002" ref-type="disp-formula" href="#jcc25364-disp-0002">2</a>), the first‐order DKH (DKH1) and IODKH have been implemented as well as the NR Hamiltonian. For the two‐electron parts, 
  <div id="nlm-math-16" class="math">
   <div class="mrow">
    <div class="msubsup">
     <span mathvariant="bold" class="mi">g</span>
     <span class="mn">2</span>
     <div class="mrow">
      <span class="mo">+</span>
      <span class="mo">+</span>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> the NR Coulomb and IODKH transformed interactions were implemented.
 </p>
